  "title": "BIM MODELLER ( M&E)",
  "description": "<h3>. BIM Modelling & Drafting</h3><ul><li><p>Develop detailed <strong>3D BIM models</strong> for M&E systems (HVAC, electrical, plumbing, fire protection, ELV).</p></li><li><p>Prepare <strong>shop drawings</strong>, layout drawings, and installation drawings from BIM models.</p></li><li><p>Model in accordance with <strong>project specifications, codes, and standards</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Convert 2D CAD drawings into accurate BIM models.</p></li></ul><h3>2. Coordination & Clash Detection</h3><ul><li><p>Perform <strong>clash detection</strong> between M&E, architectural, and structural models.</p></li><li><p>Resolve clashes in coordination meetings with consultants and contractors.</p></li><li><p>Update models based on coordination outcomes and site conditions.</p></li></ul><h3>3. Documentation & Deliverables</h3><ul><li><p>Generate <strong>construction drawings</strong>, schedules, and quantities from BIM models.</p></li><li><p>Prepare <strong>as-built drawings</strong> and models at project completion.</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper <strong>BIM documentation</strong>, model versions, and file management.</p></li></ul><h3>4. Software & Tools</h3><ul><li><p>Use BIM software such as <strong>Revit (MEP)</strong>, Navisworks, AutoCAD, and related tools.</p></li><li><p>Apply BIM standards, families, templates, and shared parameters.</p></li><li><p>Support BIM execution plans (BEP) and project BIM workflows.</p></li></ul><h3>5. Quantity Take-Off & BOQ Support</h3><ul><li><p>Extract quantities for <strong>cost estimation and material take-offs</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Assist QS and project teams with BIM-based quantity data.</p></li></ul><h3>6. Site & Construction Support</h3><ul><li><p>Coordinate with site engineers to resolve <strong>site issues using BIM models</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Update models based on <strong>site changes, RFIs, and revisions</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Provide BIM visuals to support construction planning and sequencing.</p></li></ul><h3>7. Quality Control & Compliance</h3><ul><li><p>Ensure models meet <strong>LOD requirements</strong> (LOD 300/400/500 as required).</p></li><li><p>Follow client BIM standards and international standards (ISO 19650, etc.).</p></li><li><p>Conduct internal model checks for accuracy and consistency.</p></li></ul><h3>8. Collaboration & Communication</h3><ul><li><p>Work closely with <strong>engineers, BIM coordinators, and project managers</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Participate in coordination meetings and technical discussions.</p></li><li><p>Support junior modellers when required.</p></li></ul>",
